	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Why &quot;logic&quot; is bullshit (RANT)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I really cannot stand people who use &quot;logic&quot; to excuse whatever unscientifically sound nonsensical argument they make to fit their narrative.  The whole &quot;it's logic&quot; excuse doesn't fly.  People might as well just say &quot;it's magic&quot; or &quot;I have a larger dick size, so my opinion is right&quot; because, ultimately what difference does it make?<br /><br />Another variation to the &quot;it's logic&quot; excuse, is the &quot;my argument is backed by research&quot; excuse.  What it really means is that they're arguments are backed by other people's speculation, without any personal investigation.  You might as well say &quot;somebody pointed a gun to my head and forced me to believe it.&quot;

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


