	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think that I agree, to a point... Although also I may add a couple things:<br /><br />-Life sucks, and can depress you when you least expect it (Do you think it's 42?!?), But this is my experience,<br /><br />-Logic can be random and dumb... as we know, But in the right hands (electronically speaking, for example... making NES games or even soldering logic boards onto a Computer) can be the smartest and best way to make a Game or a Computer work. Even a Business for a living!<br /><br />-Have you heard of these things called Picross/Nonogram/Oekaki puzzles, They are logic puzzles too.

		

